The course introduces the biology subject in school, its purposes and expected outcomes and the most important topics in biology. The course also introduces the ways for becoming biology teacher and everyday work as biology teacher. Critical and creative thinking, comparative analysis of biological processes and understanding of living systems, as well as self-analysis and reflection skills, time planning and career awareness are developed.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To provide an overview of biology teaching and teaching methods in general education schools, introducing biology teachers to the general learning skills they can pass on to their future students (critical and creative thinking in planning their activities; time planning skills, self-analysis and reflection skills,  and comparative analysis of biological objects and processes, understanding the life systems). The development of biology-related career awareness.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1) understands the purpose and excepted outcomes in biology as school subject,
2) has an overview of the most important topics in biology as school subject,
3) is competent to make reasoned decision for becoming biology teacher,
4) uses critical and creative thinking in planning his or her activities;
5) is able to plan his / her time when planning learning activities,
6) has obtained self-analysis and reflection skills,
7) is able to conduct  a comparative analysis of biological objects and processes and understands the functioning of life systems.
